Hi, Katie.

As Katie wrote to Dr. Math
On 09/20/2004 at 10:46:00 (Eastern Time),
>[Question]
>I get the greater than less than symbols confused.  How do I 
>remember them?
>
>[Difficulty]
>I get them backwards
>
>[Thoughts]
>

I just remember that the larger number is on the larger side of the 
symbol. So 3>2 means 3 is greater than 2, since the 3 on the left is 
bigger; 2<3 means 2 is less than 3, since the 2 on the left is 
smaller.

If you have any further questions, feel free to write back.


